title: Man charged with rape after Leeds city centre incident
title_page: Man charged with rape after Leeds city centre incident - BBC News
maintext:
A man has been charged with the rape and attempted rape of a man in West Yorkshire.
Nicholas Moco, 24, of Royal Park Avenue, Leeds, appeared before the city's magistrates' court on Saturday.
He has been charged in connection with an alleged incident outside Wharf Chambers, in Wharf Street, Leeds, at about 05:00 GMT on Saturday, 22 February.
Mr Moco was remanded in custody and will appear before Leeds Crown Court on 31 March.
